text: The latter type was far less successful, but was it really an unmitigated disaster? Its East Asian and Caribbean inheritors are remarkably successful (relative to their ethnic make-up), and Rhodesia was the jewel of Africa until it was destroyed out of political correctness. ...

... Doubt it was a net negative in India, even. Idea it was is mostly indigenous alt-history fantasizing. War-torn Mughal back-water drifting ever deeper into poverty and irrelevance was the actual alt-history version.
Yes, Anglo-Imperialism was a disaster for the Anglos, unquestionably. And, yes again, it was like slavery that way. (Ruinous for the slave-owner.)
I'm agreeing as hard as possible.
